1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,200
Indeed, our God is great, isn't He?

2
00:00:02,200 --> 00:00:08,840
And I'm so thankful that God has revealed to us in His Word who He is and that we can

3
00:00:08,840 --> 00:00:11,239
sing about His greatness.

4
00:00:11,239 --> 00:00:14,279
If you have your Bible this evening, 2 Timothy chapter number 3.

5
00:00:14,279 --> 00:00:18,700
We've been studying through the book of Ruth here on Wednesday evenings, but as I was seeking

6
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:25,719
the face of the Lord, I thought it appropriate this evening to preach a message, give a challenge,

7
00:00:25,719 --> 00:00:29,219
if you will, with regard to Scripture assembly.

8
00:00:29,219 --> 00:00:36,459
And this is our annual assembly and I've simply titled the thought this evening, the message,

9
00:00:36,459 --> 00:00:39,979
if you're taking notes, why Scripture assembly?

10
00:00:39,979 --> 00:00:40,979
Why Scripture assembly?

11
00:00:40,979 --> 00:00:42,380
Why do we do it?

12
00:00:42,380 --> 00:00:49,979
And as many of you know, we as a church, Fellowship Baptist Church, we have placed an emphasis

13
00:00:49,979 --> 00:00:51,979
on the Scripture assembly ministry.

14
00:00:51,979 --> 00:00:58,380
We've done that on purpose and we have purposed to support the printing and distribution of

15
00:00:58,380 --> 00:01:01,180
gospel literature through Beacon of Truth.

16
00:01:01,180 --> 00:01:05,959
Brother Stroop is here this evening and Brother Hummel, of course, the director, the founder

17
00:01:05,959 --> 00:01:13,019
of the ministry, God led him a number of years ago to begin this ministry by faith and part

18
00:01:13,019 --> 00:01:18,559
of what they do and really the beginning days just with gospel tracts, wanting to get literature

19
00:01:18,559 --> 00:01:19,559
put together.

20
00:01:19,559 --> 00:01:25,160
Now they do gospel tracts through full Bibles and getting that literature to missionaries

21
00:01:25,160 --> 00:01:28,519
on the mission field for the purpose of distribution.

22
00:01:28,519 --> 00:01:34,400
And of course, one of the things that they do, the way I was introduced to the ministry

23
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:37,980
was through exactly what we're doing over the next couple of days, where representatives

24
00:01:37,980 --> 00:01:42,639
from Beacon of Truth will go to a local church, they'll bring the equipment, which Brother

25
00:01:42,639 --> 00:01:45,080
Stroop didn't have to bring a whole lot of equipment this week.

26
00:01:45,080 --> 00:01:50,400
He was actually happy and that was an easy trip for him, just had to bring the raw material

27
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:54,660
and they'll bring all the equipment, they'll show up at the church and they'll be able

28
00:01:54,660 --> 00:02:00,459
to have a scripture assembly and they'll begin to show folks, I remember the very first

29
00:02:00,459 --> 00:02:04,940
time I was ever introduced to it in Pennsylvania and I remember watching Brother Dan Hummel

30
00:02:04,940 --> 00:02:09,179
stand up at the front of the church with a signature of scripture and he would show us

31
00:02:09,179 --> 00:02:15,899
how you tear it apart, how you stick it together and this is a task that anyone can do, that's

32
00:02:15,899 --> 00:02:20,279
what he said, from the youngest to the oldest, there's a job for you.

33
00:02:20,279 --> 00:02:24,100
And I remember looking at Holly, we had three small children at the time and I said, we're

34
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:29,020
going to be here for this, we're going to see what this is all about and we went.

35
00:02:29,020 --> 00:02:33,940
Joseph at the time was about two, two and a half years old and he stood next to Brother

36
00:02:33,940 --> 00:02:39,139
Dan Hummel at the cutting machine for almost the entire evening, helping Brother Hummel

37
00:02:39,139 --> 00:02:45,940
put those scriptures up on the cutting machine and from that time until now, God has really

38
00:02:45,940 --> 00:02:51,539
burdened my heart and of course, I told Brother Hummel at the time that God had called me

39
00:02:51,539 --> 00:02:55,220
to pastor, I didn't know where I'd be, I didn't know where God was going to lead us

40
00:02:55,220 --> 00:03:00,820
but one of the things that I determined was that if God would allow me to pastor a church,

41
00:03:00,820 --> 00:03:07,139
that a scripture assembly ministry was something that I believe that our church should do.

42
00:03:07,139 --> 00:03:11,500
And so I remember 12 years ago coming here and I remember the very first time I said,

43
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:15,220
we're going to have a scripture assembly and I had some folks look at me and say, what

44
00:03:15,220 --> 00:03:18,059
in the world is a scripture assembly?

45
00:03:18,059 --> 00:03:19,679
And now you're a bunch of pros, right?

46
00:03:19,679 --> 00:03:23,800
We do it all the time, we do it a couple of times a month, but I personally believe

47
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:27,759
that every church, and I know Brother Stroop would agree with this wholeheartedly, Brother

48
00:03:27,759 --> 00:03:32,720
Hummel would say, would you put that in writing and send it to everybody, but I believe personally

49
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:40,279
that every church should be involved at some level with a scripture assembly ministry.

50
00:03:40,279 --> 00:03:47,080
And I just believe that, I believe that not only is it enabling us to be able to participate

51
00:03:47,080 --> 00:03:53,919
in an aspect of the Great Commission, but what it does for a church family, the opportunity

52
00:03:53,919 --> 00:04:00,720
to fellowship around the table as you're accomplishing an eternal task, putting together the Word

53
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:03,679
of God that's going to be distributed, it's amazing.

54
00:04:03,679 --> 00:04:09,039
I speak to pastor friends regularly about a scripture assembly ministry.

55
00:04:09,039 --> 00:04:10,240
I encourage them.

56
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:14,679
I've had a number of pastors from Northern Virginia that have come to our assemblies

57
00:04:14,679 --> 00:04:20,920
over the years that have been introduced to it for the purpose of helping them understand

58
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:21,920
what we do.

59
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:27,279
And so this year, obviously, this week will be our scripture assembly ministry, our emphasis

60
00:04:27,279 --> 00:04:32,959
with our annual ministry where we have two days set aside, two sessions each day for

61
00:04:32,959 --> 00:04:38,000
the purpose of really focusing on putting the scriptures together.

62
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:40,679
But really the thought this evening is why?

63
00:04:40,679 --> 00:04:41,799
Why should we do this?

64
00:04:41,799 --> 00:04:43,640
Why do we do this?

65
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:46,760
Is it a situation that there's nothing else for us to do?

66
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:49,880
There's no other thing that we can put on our calendar?

67
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:50,880
We're bored?

68
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:51,880
We don't know?

69
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:53,679
No, that has nothing to do with it.

70
00:04:53,679 --> 00:05:00,320
In fact, there are plenty of things to do, but I believe that as we understand the vision

71
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:08,119
and the perspective that the folks at Beacon have and what we're enabled to be a part of,

72
00:05:08,119 --> 00:05:12,720
we're accomplishing great things for God and what He is able to do.

73
00:05:12,799 --> 00:05:15,799
It's kind of like what Brother Cottle said a couple of weeks ago in your Sunday school

74
00:05:15,799 --> 00:05:16,799
hour, and I wasn't here.

75
00:05:16,799 --> 00:05:21,720
I was teaching the new member class, but he and I chatted about it both on Saturday evening

76
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:23,619
and then again on Sunday afternoon.

77
00:05:23,619 --> 00:05:26,119
We are laborers together.

78
00:05:26,119 --> 00:05:32,040
And for a short period of time over these next couple of days, we have an opportunity,

79
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:38,440
spiritually speaking, to hold hands with Beacon of Truth and to accomplish something that

80
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:41,959
has the potential of impacting eternity.

81
00:05:41,959 --> 00:05:43,779
Now, that's amazing.

82
00:05:43,779 --> 00:05:48,000
When I understand it that way, when you understand it that way, I say, listen, if there's something

83
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:56,239
that I can do, that I can invest my time in, that can have an eternal impact, I want to

84
00:05:56,239 --> 00:05:57,239
know more about that.

85
00:05:57,239 --> 00:05:59,299
I want to be challenged about that.

86
00:05:59,299 --> 00:06:01,640
And so, why Scripture Assembly?

87
00:06:01,640 --> 00:06:04,040
Look at 2 Timothy chapter number 3.

88
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:06,160
It's a familiar passage of Scripture this evening.

89
00:06:06,160 --> 00:06:11,679
I'm going to answer the question of why Scripture Assembly with really just two thoughts tonight,

90
00:06:11,679 --> 00:06:15,000
and I hope it would be an encouragement to you and a challenge to you.

91
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:19,420
Many of you that are here this evening, you've participated in Scripture Assembly.

92
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:22,160
You already have it on your schedule to be here.

93
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:23,359
You wouldn't miss it.

94
00:06:23,359 --> 00:06:28,320
In fact, if I canceled Scripture Assembly, you'd try to fire me and find a new pastor,

95
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:30,440
and I understand how that works.

96
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:32,480
Some of you, you've never had the opportunity.

97
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:33,959
You're newer to our church.

98
00:06:33,959 --> 00:06:39,239
Maybe your work schedule hasn't allowed it, and I totally understand, and you may not

99
00:06:39,239 --> 00:06:43,000
have the opportunity even in the next couple of days to participate, but I want you to

100
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:49,959
have an understanding as to why we do this and why it is on our calendar regularly.

101
00:06:49,959 --> 00:06:55,640
In 2 Timothy 3 and verse number 14, notice the Bible says this, but continue thou in

102
00:06:55,640 --> 00:07:02,119
the things which thou hast learned and hast been assured of, knowing of whom thou hast

103
00:07:02,119 --> 00:07:03,119
learned them.

104
00:07:03,119 --> 00:07:06,880
Now, of course, you understand that all Scripture is given by inspiration of God.

105
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:09,119
We'll see that in a couple of verses.

106
00:07:09,119 --> 00:07:14,239
Humanly speaking, the apostle Paul is writing to his son in the faith, Timothy, in this

107
00:07:14,239 --> 00:07:19,679
second letter that bears the name of 2 Timothy, and he's really given him a charge.

108
00:07:19,679 --> 00:07:24,959
We see that terminology in chapter number 4 specifically, but Paul knows that at the

109
00:07:24,959 --> 00:07:26,839
time of his departure is at hand.

110
00:07:26,839 --> 00:07:32,880
He's encouraging Timothy, and he tells him to continue in verse number 14, and then in

111
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:38,799
verse 15 he says, and that from a child thou hast known the Holy Scriptures.

112
00:07:38,799 --> 00:07:42,839
Aren't you thankful that God has given us His Word?

113
00:07:42,839 --> 00:07:47,640
And Paul here refers to the Old Testament as being the Holy Scriptures.

114
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:50,399
That's what both Paul and Timothy would have had.

115
00:07:50,399 --> 00:07:55,720
In fact, we find that he refers to the Holy Scriptures, to the Bible, in verse number

116
00:07:55,720 --> 00:08:01,160
13 of chapter number 4, he refers to it as the parchments.

117
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:07,959
We find that as we read God's Word that there are a number of words or terms that are used

118
00:08:07,959 --> 00:08:10,279
to describe the Bible.

119
00:08:10,279 --> 00:08:14,640
In fact, in chapter number 4 he says not only the parchments, but in verse number 2, preach

120
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:15,640
the Word.

121
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:16,640
What's he talking about?

122
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:19,160
The Holy Scriptures, the Bible, the Word of God.

123
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:24,079
And we find that the Bible says in verse number 15, and that from a child thou hast known

124
00:08:24,079 --> 00:08:25,079
the Holy Scriptures.

125
00:08:25,079 --> 00:08:28,040
Now maybe tonight you're here and this would be true of you.

126
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:31,519
For Timothy it was true of him that from a child he knew the Holy Scriptures.

127
00:08:31,519 --> 00:08:34,880
I can't say for me that from a child I knew the Holy Scriptures.

128
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:36,719
I was not raised in a Christian home.

129
00:08:36,719 --> 00:08:40,440
My parents did not teach me the Scriptures as a child.

130
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:43,559
I'm not faulting them for that, it's just the way it was.

131
00:08:43,559 --> 00:08:47,799
But for some of you here this evening, from a child you've known the Holy Scriptures.

132
00:08:47,799 --> 00:08:51,359
For some of us here this evening, we didn't get saved until later in life and we didn't

133
00:08:51,359 --> 00:08:58,599
know them from a child, but we understand now as adults, as saved people, the extreme

134
00:08:58,599 --> 00:09:04,640
benefit of children learning at a young age the Holy Scriptures.

135
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:07,200
And we want to raise our children that way.

136
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:10,080
We want our children to raise their children that way.

137
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:13,280
We want the kids in our church to be taught the Scriptures.

138
00:09:13,599 --> 00:09:19,400
Listen, when we have children's classes, when we have children's church, it's not game time.

139
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:21,640
It's not like let's just have a snack and play a game.

140
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:27,919
No, we want to teach them the Bible because it's the Bible that's going to profit them,

141
00:09:27,919 --> 00:09:29,640
that's going to give them the instruction.

142
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:34,400
Just a few weeks ago we had our children's church program and you had the opportunity

143
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:40,880
to see firsthand the work that Jennifer and Lena do on a weekly basis of teaching the

144
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:45,440
Bible to our children in that children's church ministry.

145
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:50,320
Parents have the responsibility, but as a church, we don't want to just have game time

146
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,320
for our young people.

147
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:53,359
We want to teach them the Bible.

148
00:09:53,359 --> 00:10:00,000
Notice what he says in verse 15, which are able to make the wise unto salvation through faith.

149
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,000
which is in Christ Jesus.

150
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:04,300
Aren't you thankful that the Bible teaches us

151
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:05,659
about redemption?

152
00:10:05,659 --> 00:10:08,340
The Bible tells us about salvation.

153
00:10:08,340 --> 00:10:11,100
Listen, if you go to other sources,

154
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:12,640
if you listen to other voices

155
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:14,840
with regard to answering the question,

156
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:16,280
where are you gonna go when you die?

157
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:17,780
You're not gonna get the same answer.

158
00:10:17,780 --> 00:10:19,319
The Bible provides,

159
00:10:19,319 --> 00:10:22,319
and God has faithfully given us his word.

160
00:10:22,319 --> 00:10:23,520
And Paul says to Timothy,

161
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:26,360
you've known the Holy Scriptures from a child,

162
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:28,620
and these Holy Scriptures are able to make thee wise

163
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:30,540
into salvation through faith,

164
00:10:30,540 --> 00:10:31,979
which is in Christ Jesus.

165
00:10:31,979 --> 00:10:36,419
Verse 16, all Scripture is given by inspiration of God.

166
00:10:36,419 --> 00:10:38,759
And it's profitable for doctrine,

167
00:10:38,759 --> 00:10:40,520
for reproof, for correction,

168
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:42,459
for instruction in righteousness,

169
00:10:42,459 --> 00:10:45,259
that the man of God may be perfect,

170
00:10:45,259 --> 00:10:49,560
throughly furnished unto all good works.

171
00:10:49,560 --> 00:10:52,840
Now this is a familiar passage of Scripture this evening,

172
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:54,779
but if I could answer the question,

173
00:10:54,779 --> 00:10:57,139
and I'll look at this passage and one other,

174
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:59,200
if I could answer the question this evening,

175
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:01,500
why Scripture assembly?

176
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:04,879
Number one, and go to Acts chapter number one, if you will.

177
00:11:04,879 --> 00:11:07,980
Number one, the first reason that I would give you,

178
00:11:07,980 --> 00:11:10,139
and I could give you a whole lot of reasons.

179
00:11:10,139 --> 00:11:12,120
I'm gonna give you two this evening.

180
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:15,819
The first answer to the question of why Scripture assembly

181
00:11:15,819 --> 00:11:19,779
is because of the command that's been given to us

182
00:11:19,779 --> 00:11:22,319
to reach the world with the gospel.

183
00:11:22,319 --> 00:11:23,800
We have been given a command.

184
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:26,500
We often refer to it as the Great Commission,

185
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:28,819
and we find that in the gospel accounts,

186
00:11:28,819 --> 00:11:30,599
we see that the Lord Jesus Christ

187
00:11:30,599 --> 00:11:34,059
gave the Great Commission, and we've been commanded.

188
00:11:34,059 --> 00:11:35,839
In fact, this past Sunday morning

189
00:11:35,839 --> 00:11:38,139
in our new member Sunday school class,

190
00:11:38,139 --> 00:11:40,779
I dealt with the subject of the Great Commission

191
00:11:40,779 --> 00:11:42,279
and personal evangelism,

192
00:11:42,279 --> 00:11:45,540
and I said this to those folks in that class,

193
00:11:45,540 --> 00:11:48,339
not only is it a responsibility, but it's a privilege.

194
00:11:48,339 --> 00:11:50,739
And really, when we look at the Great Commission

195
00:11:50,739 --> 00:11:54,319
as being a privilege that I am allowed of God

196
00:11:54,339 --> 00:11:56,540
to be able to share the gospel,

197
00:11:56,540 --> 00:11:58,620
that really changes, that perspective

198
00:11:58,620 --> 00:12:00,580
changes our approach to it.

199
00:12:00,580 --> 00:12:03,319
But this evening, when I say why Scripture assembly,

200
00:12:03,319 --> 00:12:05,419
because of the command to reach the world with the gospel.

201
00:12:05,419 --> 00:12:07,480
We've been given a command

202
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:09,759
to reach the world with the gospel.

203
00:12:09,759 --> 00:12:12,919
Now, in of ourselves, that's a task that's impossible.

204
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:17,800
But I'm thankful that God said he would be with us.

205
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:22,500
He enables us, and I'm thankful that God gave us a plan

206
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:25,259
for how we can labor together

207
00:12:25,259 --> 00:12:28,059
in order to accomplish the Great Commission.

208
00:12:28,059 --> 00:12:30,000
Now, working with Beacon of Truth

209
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:32,000
and the Scripture assembly ministry

210
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:34,600
does not give us the,

211
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:38,440
this is satisfying completely our responsibility

212
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:40,399
with fulfilling the Great Commission,

213
00:12:40,399 --> 00:12:42,199
but I would submit to you this evening

214
00:12:42,199 --> 00:12:45,539
that it is an avenue that allows us

215
00:12:45,539 --> 00:12:49,979
to accomplish what God has commanded us to do.

216
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,660
Look at Acts chapter one and verse number eight.

217
00:12:52,660 --> 00:12:54,300
We're familiar with the Great Commission.

218
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:56,039
Notice what the Bible says here.

219
00:12:56,039 --> 00:12:58,880
This is the Lord Jesus Christ speaking to the disciples

220
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:01,139
before he ascended to heaven.

221
00:13:01,139 --> 00:13:02,419
He's already gone to the cross.

222
00:13:02,419 --> 00:13:04,320
He's resurrected from the dead.

223
00:13:04,320 --> 00:13:07,119
He's giving some final instruction

224
00:13:07,119 --> 00:13:08,979
before he would ascend to heaven.

225
00:13:08,979 --> 00:13:10,820
In fact, in just a few verses

226
00:13:10,820 --> 00:13:12,720
beyond what we'll read this evening,

227
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:14,960
you read of that ascension

228
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:18,960
and also the wonderful promise that Jesus will come again.

229
00:13:18,979 --> 00:13:20,240
And what a joy that is.

230
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:21,440
But notice in verse number eight,

231
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:22,279
the Bible says,

232
00:13:22,279 --> 00:13:25,919
but ye shall receive power

233
00:13:25,919 --> 00:13:28,919
after that the Holy Ghost has come upon you.

234
00:13:28,919 --> 00:13:31,020
I'm thankful that we don't go on our own power.

235
00:13:31,020 --> 00:13:33,360
We go on the power of the Holy Ghost.

236
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:37,399
And it says, and ye shall be witnesses unto me.

237
00:13:37,399 --> 00:13:39,839
